Mafdet is a fortified harbor city where the Saltglass Reach meets the open sea.
It serves as the gateway between inland civilization and ocean trade.
Named after a pre-Keeper coastal ritual figure: a swift feline executioner who punished oath-breakers.
Every citizen carries a guardian-name alongside their given name, a mark of accountability from ancient watch cults.
Trade oaths are sealed at the Shrine of the First Claw on a basalt sculpture. Breaking such an oath is the gravest commercial crime in the port.
Dual-attestation protocol: no cargo moves without verification under both inland provenance and maritime risk standards.
Four Ledger Houses certify manifests. The Quarantine Ledger classifies pyramid-origin artifacts by hazard level using a four-tier system descended from Khar'Daan's containment procedures.
Three power blocs share governance under the Strandline Compact: Harbor Wardens (quay security, harbor chain), Ledger Houses (documents, conversion rates), Sand-Sea Carters' Guild (overland linkage to oasis corridors).
Signal towers are the first landmark arriving ships see; the Shrine's claw-marked spire is the second.
Mafdet asks no questions about origin, only about cargo. It pays fairly and heals without prejudice.
